You <em>must</em> include the following when saving your CI. If you don't it will error <em>silently</em>. It will appear to have worked but in effect it does nothing. If it errors it won't tell you.
<pre><code>
      If Not (&amp;myCI.Save()) Then
         Local any &amp;COLL = %Session.PSMessages;
         For &amp;i = 1 To &amp;COLL.Count
            Local any &amp;ERROR = &amp;COLL.Item(&amp;i);
            Local any &amp;TEXT = &amp;ERROR.Text;
            MessageBox(0, "", 0, 0, &amp;ERROR | " " | &amp;TEXT);
         End-For;
         &amp;COLL.DeleteAll();
      End-If;
</code></pre>
Also, to avoid going mad I recommend setting the following property of your CI. Things like &amp;itmSomeTable.Count don't get updated in real time otherwise! You'll insert rows and won't see this value update until <em>after</em> you save.
<pre><code>      
    &amp;myCI.InteractiveMode = True;
</code></pre>

Simple example of controlling whether a Field is required using PeopleCode instead of the Record definition properties.

Place this in the Record Field's SaveEdit PeopleCode.
<pre style="background-color:#eeeeee;border:1px dashed #999999;color:black;font-family:Andale Mono, Lucida Console, Monaco, fixed, monospace;font-size:12px;line-height:14px;overflow:auto;padding:5px;width:100%;"><code>
If GetRowset()ActiveRowCount &gt; 1 Then
   If None(GetField().Value) Then
      GetField().SetCursorPos(%Page);
      GetField().Style = "PSERROR";
      Error MsgGet(15, 30, "Highlighted fields are required.");
   Else
      GetField().Style = "PSEDITBOX";
   End-If;
End-If;
</code></pre>

